%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Federal%20Deposit%20Insurance%20Corporation%2C%20or%20FDIC%2C%20has%20a%20%26quot%3Bpatriarchal%26quot%3B%20culture%2C%20according%20to%20an%20independent%20report.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20bank%20regulator%20took%20no%20action%20on%20dozens%20of%20harassment%20complaints%20and%20moved%20wrongdoers%20around.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInvestigators%20raised%20doubts%20about%20the%20FDIC%20chairman's%20ability%20to%20lead%20a%20cultural%20transformation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20key%20US%20bank%20regulator%20has%20a%20%26quot%3Bpatriarchal%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Binsular%26quot%3B%20culture%20and%20is%20led%20by%20a%20chairman%20with%20a%20reputation%20for%20a%20strong%20temper%2C%20according%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fdic.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-05%2Fcleary-report-to-fdic-src.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindependent%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20234-page%20summary%20of%20the%20months-long%20investigation%2C%20led%20by%20the%20external%20law%20firm%20Cleary%20Gottlieb%20Steen%20%26amp%3B%20Hamilton%2C%20highlighted%20longstanding%20and%20recent%20issues%20at%20the%20Federal%20Deposit%20Insurance%20Corporation%2C%20or%20FDIC.%20The%20report%20said%20the%20FDIC%20has%20dismissed%20myriad%20harassment%20complaints%20and%20that%20wrongdoers%20are%20moved%20around%20internally%20or%20promoted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20firm's%20report%20builds%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fus-news%2Ffdic-toxic-atmosphere-strip-clubs-lewd-photos-boozy-hotel-12c89da7%3Fmod%3Darticle_inline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edamning%20November%20story%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20about%20the%20FDIC's%20toxic%20work%20culture%20and%20comes%20as%20the%20FDIC%20faces%20a%20probe%20from%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestigators%20said%20they%20set%20up%20a%20hotline%20in%20mid-January%20and%20received%20more%20than%20500%20complaints%20%E2%80%94%20largely%20from%20current%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20about%20sexual%20harassment%2C%20discrimination%2C%20and%20other%20issues.%20The%20FDIC%20has%20about%206%2C000%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETuesday's%20report%20characterized%20the%20FDIC's%20culture%20as%20%26quot%3B'misogynistic%2C'%20'patriarchal%2C'%20'insular%2C'%20and%20'outdated'%E2%80%94a%20'good%20ol'%20boys'%20club%20where%20favoritism%20is%20common%2C%20wagons%20are%20circled%20around%20managers%2C%20and%20senior%20executives%20with%20well-known%20reputations%20for%20pursuing%20romantic%20relations%20with%20subordinates%20enjoy%20long%20careers%20without%20any%20apparent%20consequence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20FDIC%20operates%20an%20anti-harassment%20program%2C%20the%20report%20said%20it%20is%20ineffective.%20Of%20the%2092%20complaints%20the%20FDIC%20received%20from%202015%20through%202023%2C%20none%20resulted%20in%20more%20serious%20discipline%20than%20a%20suspension%20%E2%80%94%20and%20only%20two%20warranted%20suspensions%2C%20while%2078%20led%20to%20no%20discipline.%20Investigators%20said%20many%20employees%20did%20not%20report%20issues%20because%20they%20feared%20retaliation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestigators%20spoke%20with%20one%20employee%20who%20said%20she%20%26quot%3Bfeared%20deeply%20for%20her%20physical%20safety%26quot%3B%20after%20her%20colleague%2C%20who%20was%20stalking%20her%2C%20kept%20texting%20her%20sexually%20explicit%20messages%2C%20even%20after%20she%20made%20a%20complaint%20against%20him.%20Staff%20from%20underrepresented%20groups%20said%20they%20were%20told%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Btoken%26quot%3B%20employees%20meant%20to%20fill%20quotas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETuesday's%20investigation%20builds%20on%20a%202020%20report%20from%20the%20FDIC's%20inspector%20general%20that%20found%20the%20regulator%20had%20not%20created%20an%20%26quot%3Badequate%26quot%3B%20sexual%20harassment%20reporting%20and%20prevention%20program.%20The%20earlier%20report%20also%20noted%20widespread%20fear%20of%20retaliation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20independent%20investigators%20spent%20nine%20pages%20discussing%20FDIC%20chairman%20Martin%20Gruenberg's%20conduct.%20Investigators%20wrote%20that%20they%20heard%20%26quot%3Bcredible%20reports%26quot%3B%20of%20Gruenberg's%20temper%2C%20including%20in%20meetings%20as%20recently%20as%20May%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20the%20FDIC%20faces%20a%20crisis%20relating%20to%20its%20workplace%20culture%2C%20Chairman%20Gruenberg's%20reputation%20raises%20questions%20about%20the%20credibility%20of%20the%20leadership's%20response%20to%20the%20crisis%20and%20the%20'moral%20authority'%20to%20lead%20a%20cultural%20transformation%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGruenberg%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20Tuesday%20to%20employees%2C%20released%20to%20the%20public%2C%20that%20he%20took%20responsibility%20for%20the%20agency%2C%20including%20its%20culture.%20The%2071-year-old%20Democrat%20has%20spent%20nearly%20a%20decade%20in%20the%20role%20under%20multiple%20presidential%20administrations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20also%20want%20to%20apologize%20for%20any%20shortcomings%20on%20my%20part%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20report's%20publication%2C%20some%20lawmakers%20from%20both%20parties%20called%20for%20Gruenberg's%20exit.%20His%20departure%20would%20put%20vice%20chairman%20Travis%20Hill%2C%20a%20Republican%2C%20in%20the%20interim%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20White%20House%20press%20secretary%20Karine%20Jean-Pierre%20didn't%20say%20whether%20the%20president%20still%20has%20confidence%20in%20Gruenberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20Gruenberg%20%26quot%3Bapologized%20and%20has%20committed%20to%20the%20recommendations%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20law%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FDIC%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esent%20outside%20standard%20hours.%20The%20agency%20has%20not%20issued%20a%20statement%20beyond%20Gruenberg's%20Tuesday%20message%20to%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffdic-toxic-work-culture-independent-report-leadership-gruenberg-probe-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715147658000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663b10fa9686a6f37bfd1955%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffdic-toxic-work-culture-independent-report-leadership-gruenberg-probe-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20bank%20regulator%20took%20no%20action%20on%20dozens%20of%20recent%20harassment%20complaints%20and%20moved%20wrongdoers%20around.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Meghan%20Morris)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffdic-toxic-work-culture-independent-report-leadership-gruenberg-probe-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meet%20Mona%20Patel%2C%20The%20Entrepreneur%20Making%20Waves%20With%20Her%20Met%20Gala%20Debut%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EEntrepreneur%20and%20philanthropist%20Mona%20Patel%20recently%20made%20heads%20turn%20at%20the%20Met%20Gala%202024.%20Styled%20by%20the%20renowned%20Law%20Roach%2C%20Ms%20Patel%20stunned%20attendees%20with%20her%20elegant%20nude%20gown%2C%20aligning%20with%20the%20Gala's%20theme%20%26quot%3BThe%20Garden%20of%20Time%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20floor-length%20dress%2C%20created%20by%20designer%C2%A0Iris%20Van%20Herpen's%20team%20in%20India%2C%C2%A0had%20a%20stunning%20butterfly-shaped%20corset%20and%20a%20trailing%20train%20affixed%20with%20mechanical%20butterflies%20that%20fluttered%20their%20wings%20with%20her%20every%20step.%20She%20designed%20the%203D%20butterflies%20herself%20with%20the%20help%20of%C2%A0kinetic%20motion%20artist%20Casey%20Cu