p%3EA%20recent%20survey%20reveals%20a%20clear%20shift%20in%20communication%20preferences.%20Texting%20reigns%20supreme%2C%20with%20over%2070%25%20of%20young%20adults%20favouring%20it.%20Voice%20notes%20are%20also%20gaining%20traction%2C%20being%20preferred%20by%20nearly%2040%25.%20This%20trend%20seems%20linked%20to%20a%20general%20dislike%20of%20unexpected%20calls%3B%20more%20than%20half%20associate%20them%20with%20bad%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20this%20aversion%20to%20phone%20calls%20isn't%20shared%20by%20older%20demographics.%20Only%201%25%20of%20those%20aged%2035-54%20prioritise%20texts%20over%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20suggests%20a%20generational%20shift%20in%20communication%20styles.%20Phone%20calls%2C%20once%20a%20revolutionary%20tool%20for%20connection%2C%20are%20seemingly%20declining%20in%20favour%20of%20asynchronous%20methods%20like%20texting%20and%20voice%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20reported%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmetro.co.uk%2F2024%2F05%2F07%2Fa-quarter-gen-z-never-answered-a-phone-call-20790257%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Metro%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20younger%20demographic%20has%20played%20a%20notable%20role%20in%20the%20accumulation%20of%201.3%20trillion%20online%20messages%20and%2036%20billion%20text%20messages%20exchanged%20in%20the%20UK%20from%202012%20to%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20prevalent%20explanation%20for%20their%20reluctance%20to%20answer%20phone%20calls%20is%20the%20perceived%20pressure%20associated%20with%20them.%20More%20than%20half%20of%20them%20anticipate%20negative%20news%20when%20receiving%20unexpected%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYounger%20individuals%20generally%20prefer%20scheduled%20phone%20conversations%20as%20the%20primary%20means%20of%20communication.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Cary%20Cooper%2C%20an%20organisational%20psychologist%2C%20affirmed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finews.co.uk%2Finews-lifestyle%2Fdeath-of-phone-call-transformed-work-3038615%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EiNews%20UK%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20decline%20in%20phone%20calls%20is%20indeed%20occurring.%20However%2C%20he%20suggests%20it%20presents%20a%20double-edged%20sword%20for%20our%20mental%20wellness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20ideal%20in%20working%20relationships%20is%20face-to-face%2C%20but%20we're%20spread%20out%2C%20we're%20working%20hybridly%2C%20and%20we're%20not%20in%20the%20office%20as%20much%20as%20we%20were%20pre-pandemic%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explains%20on%20a%20spontaneous%20phone%20call.%20Cooper%20adds%20that%20where%20face-to-face%20isn't%20possible%2C%20the%20nearest%20you%20can%20get%20to%20it%20is%20better%3A%20video%20is%20better%20than%20audio%2C%20and%20audio%20is%20better%20than%20text.%20The%20worst%20of%20all%20worlds%2C%20though%2C%20is%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715144580000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2016-07%2Fphone-call-generic_650x400_41468847173.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fa-quarter-of-gen-z-and-millennials-have-never-answered-a-phone-call-survey-finds-5614889%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20recent%20survey%20reveals%20a%20clear%20shift%20in%20communication%20preferences.%20Texting%20reigns%20supreme%2C%20with%20over%2070%25%20of%20young%20adults%20favouring%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fa-quarter-of-gen-z-and-millennials-have-never-answered-a-phone-call-survey-finds-5614889%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fa-quarter-of-gen-z-and-millennials-have-never-answered-a-phone-call-survey-finds-5614889%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fa-quarter-of-gen-z-and-millennials-have-never-answered-a-phone-call-survey-finds-5614889%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SXSW%20Festival%20to%20Expand%20with%20Launch%20of%20London%20Editio